{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/a-coding-cure-for-our-current-coronavirus-culture-57d6df4527dd", "time": 1683004939.680185, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/a-coding-cure-for-our-current-coronavirus-culture-57d6df4527dd/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "A Coding Cure. Yes, it\u2019s serious. | by Tony Bosco | Towards Data Science", "h1": "A Coding Cure", "description": "Yes, it\u2019s hard to be distracted from it when you can\u2019t go out and escape it, and every news program commandeers every station to talk about it. Thank you, Coronavirus, for making us all extras in\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://generalassemb.ly/", "anchor_text": "General Assembly", "paragraph_index": 20}, {"url": "https://www.udemy.com/", "anchor_text": "Udemy,", "paragraph_index": 20}, {"url": "https://www.datacamp.com/", "anchor_text": "DataCamp", "paragraph_index": 20}], "all_paragraphs": ["Yes, we should all take it seriously.", "Yes, it\u2019s hard to be distracted from it when you can\u2019t go out and escape it, and every news program commandeers every station to talk about it.", "Thank you, Coronavirus, for making us all extras in someone else\u2019s big, scary, pandemic-themed horror movie and for making us all hunker down at home in whatever rooms are now serving as our own personal panic rooms.", "It can be depressing\u2026and yet, it doesn\u2019t have to be.", "If you think about it, it\u2019s a huge opportunity as well.", "No commute. No quick walks around the office to avoid that coworker. No endless meetings. No repeated coffee runs to the corner coffee shop (you know you needed to cut back on the caffeine anyway).", "Somewhere in there, you may have just picked up at least a half hour to maybe, if you are lucky, an hour a day.", "Whether you are curious about coding or getting interested in a career in Data Science or UX/UI, why not take the time to invest in yourself and pick up those exceptional coding skills you keep promising yourself you are going to acquire?", "We\u2019re being told right now we might be \u201clivin\u2019 la vida lockdown\u201d for at least a month, so maybe it\u2019s time to make the best of your situation and learn a couple of really valuable programming languages that you can leverage on the other side of the outbreak.", "So, if you have been thinking about it, here\u2019s Dr. Bosco\u2019s prescription for the cure for our common Coronavirus culture \u2014 take one of these online daily and call me in the morning (and if you are feeling really good about it, take two):", "Python is not only here to stay but has grown in popularity so rapidly it will likely be the dominant programming language for years to come.", "The language itself is logical, the code is readable, and the programming syntax is simple. It can be applied to an incredibly wide range of situations such as data science, data visualization, gaming, and more.", "It is probably the most important programming language you need to get to know today and is on track to be the dominant force in programming languages tomorrow.", "Structured Query Language (SQL) is a programming language used to interact with databases and analyze and understand that data through queries.", "It is in really high demand right now because many companies are using it to run queries and perform analysis on the data they tap into. Chances are the company you are currently working for is using it, and the company you hope to work for someday is leveraging it as well.", "From big companies like Google and Amazon, or medium sized companies, SQL is everywhere as are courses to help you get to know it quickly.", "One of the most popular programming languages in the world, JavaScript, is an object orient programming language designed to simplify web development.", "It allows you to bring life to the elements you set on a web page by making them interactive. You can use it to create menus, animations, maps, and video players.", "JavaScript is used in the development of webpages, mobile apps, browser-based games, and more. There is so much out there waiting to be created with JavaScript, and many companies willing to pay you to get it done.", "You are just a Google search away from an intimidating list of hundreds of links to courses claiming they would be able to shepherd you through learning code, so allow me to help you narrow things down a bit.", "I\u2019ve been very partial to the experiences I have had with General Assembly, Udemy, and DataCamp. Please note, there are no paid endorsements here, only my personal experience.", "I\u2019d suggest you start reviewing each of them and make your own decisions based on what you want to learn, how things sync up with your own learning style and work schedule, and what you may wish to achieve with your new-found coding knowledge once the Coronavirus culture finally subsides.", "We all need to stay optimistic.", "We will get better, and now we can use this time to learn how to code so we can all be a little better at what we do.", "Then we can all leverage our new skills to make the world a little better too.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "As an experienced marketer and business consultant to global brands, Tony embraced Data Science to drive new insights and visualize opportunities for growth."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F57d6df4527dd&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fa-coding-cure-for-our-current-coronavirus-culture-57d6df4527dd&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=htt